  "text": "Then, the expression of HMGB1 and its subsequent signaling pathway mediators were detected by IHC, qPCR and ELISA, in order to explore the underlying molecular mechanisms of early renal injury. IHC staining demonstrated that the overall expression and the expression in the cytoplasm of the HMGB1 protein was increased in the hypoxia groups compared with the controls. This suggested that hypoxia may upregulate the expression of HMGB1, and may also increase its the nuclear translocation (from nucleus to cytoplasm); this is where the HMGB1 protein is then acetylated to its active form in the cytoplasm [CITATION_1] . An increased expression of HMGB1 in the cytoplasm suggested an increase in HMGB1 activity.",
